Make a paste from the garlic and ginger in a food blender.Heat the oil in a non-stick pan and add the spice mix.Add the ginger and garlic paste to the pan. Cook on a high heat for 5-6 minutes, or until it turns light brown. Add the ground turmeric, red Kashmiri chilli paste, tomato pur√©e and salt, to taste.Add the boneless chicken and mix well. Cook for 10-15 minutes on a medium heat, or until the chicken is cooked through, stirring occasionally.Serve with plain boiled rice or chapatti.